    <fr:title text="Equivalent conditions to be an eigenvalue">Equivalent conditions to be an eigenvalue</fr:title>
    <fr:taxon>theorem</fr:taxon>
    <fr:meta name="source"><fr:link href="/axler-1996-linear/" title="Linear Algebra Done Right" uri="http://localhost:8000/axler-1996-linear/" display-uri="axler-1996-linear" type="local">Linear Algebra Done Right</fr:link> Theorem 5.7</fr:meta>
    <fr:meta name="source"><fr:link href="/lankham-2016-linear/" title="Linear algebra as an introduction to abstract mathematics" uri="http://localhost:8000/lankham-2016-linear/" display-uri="lankham-2016-linear" type="local">Linear algebra as an introduction to abstract mathematics</fr:link> Section 7.2</fr:meta>
  </fr:frontmatter>
  <fr:mainmatter>
    <html:p>Let <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[V]]></fr:tex> be a finite-dimensional vector space over <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\mathbb {F}]]></fr:tex>. Let <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[L\colon  V\to  V]]></fr:tex> be a linear operator. Let <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\lambda \in \mathbb {F}]]></fr:tex>. Then the following are equivalent:</html:p>
    <html:ol><html:li><fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\lambda ]]></fr:tex> is an <fr:link href="/vectsp-001P/" title="Invariant subspace" uri="http://localhost:8000/vectsp-001P/" display-uri="vectsp-001P" type="local">eigenvalue</fr:link> of <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[L]]></fr:tex></html:li>
<html:li><fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[L-\lambda  I]]></fr:tex> is not <fr:link href="/ela-001J/" title="Injective function" uri="http://localhost:8000/ela-001J/" display-uri="ela-001J" type="local">injective</fr:link></html:li>
<html:li><fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[L-\lambda  I]]></fr:tex> is not <fr:link href="/ela-001I/" title="Surjective function" uri="http://localhost:8000/ela-001I/" display-uri="ela-001I" type="local">surjective</fr:link></html:li>
<html:li><fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[L-\lambda  I]]></fr:tex> is not invertible</html:li></html:ol>
  </fr:mainmatter>
