                <fr:title text="Existence of eigenvalues">Existence of eigenvalues</fr:title>
                <fr:taxon>theorem</fr:taxon>
                <fr:meta name="source"><fr:link href="/axler-1996-linear/" title="Linear Algebra Done Right" uri="http://localhost:8000/axler-1996-linear/" display-uri="axler-1996-linear" type="local">Linear Algebra Done Right</fr:link> Theorem 5.19</fr:meta>
                <fr:meta name="source"><fr:link href="/lankham-2016-linear/" title="Linear algebra as an introduction to abstract mathematics" uri="http://localhost:8000/lankham-2016-linear/" display-uri="lankham-2016-linear" type="local">Linear algebra as an introduction to abstract mathematics</fr:link> Theorem 7.4.1</fr:meta>
              </fr:frontmatter>
              <fr:mainmatter><html:p>Let <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[V\neq \{0\}]]></fr:tex> be a <fr:link href="/vectsp-000O/" title="Finite-Dimensional Vector Space" uri="http://localhost:8000/vectsp-000O/" display-uri="vectsp-000O" type="local">Finite-Dimensional Vector Space</fr:link> over <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\mathbb {C}]]></fr:tex>. Let <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[L\colon  V\to  V]]></fr:tex> be a linear operator. Then <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[L]]></fr:tex> has at least one eigenvalue.</html:p>
 
   
   <fr:tree show-metadata="false" toc="false"><fr:frontmatter><fr:authors><fr:author><fr:link href="/alex-nelson/" title="Alex Nelson" uri="http://localhost:8000/alex-nelson/" display-uri="alex-nelson" type="local">Alex Nelson</fr:link></fr:author></fr:authors><fr:date><fr:year>2025</fr:year><fr:month>12</fr:month><fr:day>10</fr:day></fr:date><fr:taxon>proof</fr:taxon></fr:frontmatter><fr:mainmatter><html:p>Let <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[n=\dim (V)]]></fr:tex>, let <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[v\in  V]]></fr:tex> be a nonzero vector. We have the collection of vectors
<fr:tex display="block"><![CDATA[\{V, Tv, T^{2}v, …, T^{n}v\}]]></fr:tex>
Since this contains <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[n+1]]></fr:tex> vectors, it must be <fr:link href="/vectsp-000Q/" title="Linearly Independent Vectors" uri="http://localhost:8000/vectsp-000Q/" display-uri="vectsp-000Q" type="local">linearly dependent</fr:link>. Then there exists scalars <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[a_{0},a_{1},…,a_{n}\in \mathbb {C}]]></fr:tex> not all zero, such that
<fr:tex display="block"><![CDATA[0=a_{0}v+a_{1}Lv+a_{2}L^{2}v+…+a_{n}L^{n}v]]></fr:tex>
Let <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[m]]></fr:tex> be the largest index such that <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[a_{m}\neq 0]]></fr:tex> (so all <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[a_{k}=0]]></fr:tex> for <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[k>m]]></fr:tex> and we can just drop these terms). Since <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[v\neq 0]]></fr:tex>, we must have <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[m>0]]></fr:tex> (and even possibly <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[m=n]]></fr:tex>). Consider the polynomial
<fr:tex display="block"><![CDATA[p(z)=a_{0}+a_{1}z+…+a_{m}z^{m}.]]></fr:tex>
Then using the <fr:link href="/complex-000N/" title="" uri="http://localhost:8000/complex-000N/" display-uri="complex-000N" type="local">immediate consequences</fr:link> of the fundamental theorem of algebra, we can factorize <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[p(z)]]></fr:tex> as
<fr:tex display="block"><![CDATA[p(z)=c(z-\lambda _{1})(…)(z-\lambda _{m})]]></fr:tex>
where <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[c,\lambda _{1},…,\lambda _{m}\in \mathbb {C}]]></fr:tex> and <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[c\neq 0]]></fr:tex>.</html:p>
<html:p>Then
<fr:tex display="block"><![CDATA[0=a_{0}v+a_{1}Lv+a_{2}L^{2}v+…+a_{n}L^{n}v=p(L)v]]></fr:tex>
and
<fr:tex display="block"><![CDATA[0=p(L)v=c(L-\lambda _{1}I)(…)(L-\lambda _{m}I)v]]></fr:tex>
which means at least one of the factors <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[L-\lambda _{j}I]]></fr:tex> must be non-injective. This means <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\lambda _{j}]]></fr:tex> must be an eigenvalue of <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[L]]></fr:tex>.</html:p><html:span class="qed">∎</html:span></fr:mainmatter></fr:tree>
 
</fr:mainmatter>
            </fr:tree>
