                <fr:title text="Criteria for linear operator to have an upper-triangular matrix">Criteria for linear operator to have an upper-triangular matrix</fr:title>
                <fr:taxon>theorem</fr:taxon>
                <fr:meta name="source"><fr:link href="/axler-1996-linear/" title="Linear Algebra Done Right" uri="http://localhost:8000/axler-1996-linear/" display-uri="axler-1996-linear" type="local">Linear Algebra Done Right</fr:link> Theorem 5.39</fr:meta>
                <fr:meta name="source"><fr:link href="/lankham-2016-linear/" title="Linear algebra as an introduction to abstract mathematics" uri="http://localhost:8000/lankham-2016-linear/" display-uri="lankham-2016-linear" type="local">Linear algebra as an introduction to abstract mathematics</fr:link> Proposition 7.5.2</fr:meta>
              </fr:frontmatter>
              <fr:mainmatter>
                <html:p>Let <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[V]]></fr:tex> be a <fr:link href="/vectsp-000O/" title="Finite-Dimensional Vector Space" uri="http://localhost:8000/vectsp-000O/" display-uri="vectsp-000O" type="local">Finite-Dimensional Vector Space</fr:link> over <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\mathbb {F}]]></fr:tex> with <fr:link href="/vectsp-000T/" title="Basis of vector space" uri="http://localhost:8000/vectsp-000T/" display-uri="vectsp-000T" type="local">basis</fr:link> <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[v_{1}]]></fr:tex>, …, <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[v_{n}]]></fr:tex>. Let <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[L\colon  V\to  V]]></fr:tex> be a linear operator. Then the following are equivalent:</html:p>
                <html:ol><html:li>The matrix <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[M(L)]]></fr:tex> with respect to <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[(v_{1},…,v_{n})]]></fr:tex> is an <fr:link href="/matrix-000B/" title="Upper-triangular matrix" uri="http://localhost:8000/matrix-000B/" display-uri="matrix-000B" type="local">Upper-triangular matrix</fr:link>.</html:li>
<html:li><fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[L(v_{k})\in \mathrm {span}(v_{1},…,v_{k})]]></fr:tex> for each <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[k=1,…,n]]></fr:tex></html:li>
<html:li><fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\mathrm {span}(v_{1},…,v_{k})]]></fr:tex> is <fr:link href="/vectsp-001P/" title="Invariant subspace" uri="http://localhost:8000/vectsp-001P/" display-uri="vectsp-001P" type="local">invariant</fr:link> under <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[L]]></fr:tex> for each <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[k=1,2,…,n]]></fr:tex></html:li></html:ol>
              </fr:mainmatter>
